    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-19T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-19T06:00:00-05:00" n="412"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4290: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1"
                            type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-19T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 19, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 19—8:25
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. The French delegation informs me that they are advised that <persName
                        corresp="#p_JNT1">Johnson</persName> has instructions not to cooperate at
                    Shanghai in the endeavor to arrange an armistice. On the contrary the British
                    information, though not so recent, is to the effect that <persName
                        corresp="#p_JNT1">Johnson</persName> is cooperating. Please inform me as to
                    facts if convenient.</p>
                <p>General impression here is that efforts for the moment should be concentrated on
                    obtaining an armistice but that the distance of neutral zone, 20 kilometers,
                    demanded by the Japanese is exorbitant and Japanese should be pressed to reduce
                    it to reasonable distance, perhaps 1 kilometer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
